      "writtenOn": "2017-08-28T21:39:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good thought. Since they each use different keys, the per-key locking will not deadlock. Both will hit a critical section that touches the shared LRU cache data, but that operation happens *after* the Maker. So in that situation, we should see:\n\ngetCachedCerts \u003d\u003e Lock(Key_0) \u003d\u003e Maker_certs \u003d\u003e getCachedInfo \u003d\u003e Lock(Key_1) \u003d\u003e Maker_info \u003d\u003e Get Info \u003d\u003e LRUPut(0, info) \u003d\u003e Unlock(Key_1) \u003d\u003e LRUPut(1, certs) \u003d\u003e Unlock(Key_0).\n\nSo as long as we\u0027re not reentrant on the same key, we should not be deadlocking.",
